sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Service as Registry Service<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Proxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant REST as REST Container<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant DB as PostgreSQL/MySQL<br/>5432/3306 TCP

    Note over Client,DB: Flow 1: Authenticated Model Registry Query (REST API)

    Client->>Router: POST /api/model_registry/v1alpha3/registered_models<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    Router->>Service: Forward HTTPS (re-encrypted)<br/>TLS 1.2+
    Service->>Proxy: HTTPS Request<br/>Port 8443/TCP
    Proxy->>Proxy: Validate Bearer Token<br/>(SubjectAccessReview)
    Proxy->>REST: HTTP Request (localhost)<br/>Port 8080/TCP
    REST->>DB: Query model metadata<br/>TLS (optional) + Password/Cert
    DB-->>REST: Metadata result
    REST-->>Proxy: JSON Response
    Proxy-->>Service: JSON Response
    Service-->>Router: HTTPS Response
    Router-->>Client: HTTPS Response

    Note over Client,DB: Flow 2: Internal gRPC Call

    participant InternalClient as Internal Client Pod
    participant GRPCService as Registry Service<br/>9090/TCP
    participant GRPC as gRPC Container<br/>9090/TCP gRPC

    InternalClient->>GRPCService: gRPC ml_metadata.MetadataStoreService<br/>Port 9090/TCP
    GRPCService->>GRPC: Forward to gRPC container
    GRPC->>DB: Query ML Metadata<br/>PostgreSQL/MySQL Protocol
    DB-->>GRPC: Metadata artifacts
    GRPC-->>GRPCService: gRPC Response
    GRPCService-->>InternalClient: gRPC Response

    Note over Client,DB: Flow 3: Operator Reconciliation

    participant ControllerMgr as Controller Manager
    participant APIServer as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+

    User[User]->>APIServer: kubectl apply ModelRegistry CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    APIServer->>ControllerMgr: Watch event (CR created)<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    ControllerMgr->>APIServer: Create Deployment (REST+gRPC)<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    ControllerMgr->>APIServer: Create Service<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    ControllerMgr->>APIServer: Create Route (if enabled)<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    ControllerMgr->>APIServer: Update CR status<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    APIServer-->>ControllerMgr: Success
